						<summary>

						<p>This inscription has been surmised to belong to <hi rend="bold">Uttama-Chōḷa.</hi> It registers a gift of land for burning a lamp in the temple at Tiruneyttānam by one Koṟṟaṉ Arumoḻi <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> Vānavaṉ Pēraraiyaṉ of Āṟṟūr in Māṅgāḍu-nāḍu after purchasing the same for 25 <hi rend="italic">kaḻañju</hi> of gold. Mention is also made of a land which had been presented to the same temple by <hi rend="bold">Naṅgai Varaguṇa-Perumānār</hi>, wife of the Koḍumbāḷūr chief <hi rend="bold">Parāntaka Iḷaṅgōvēḷār.</hi></p>						

						</summary>
